OL,3,CSt Helier Constable backs
OL,4,Cinvestigation into Lido tender process
OL,6,FOne of its governors, Giles Robson,
OL,7,Fsays they were not given enough time
OL,8,Fto go through the details of the
OL,9,Fcommercial lease and were refused an
OL,10,Fextension.
OL,12,FHe wants a "thorough investigation
OL,13,Finto the lease process".
OL,15,FGiles explains: "The process was quite
OL,16,Fsimply too rushed and flawed for us to
OL,17,Fdo our jobs properly, our due
OL,18,Fdiligence on the site, and to make
OL,19,Fsure we did a great job."
